    <h2><font color="#000080"><!-- 2004-08-31 -->
    
    Moving Peano Ahead for OOPSLA
    
    </font></h2>
    
    
    <p>
	<div style="clear:both;"></div><p><small>Thanks to a February 16 post&nbsp;by <a href="http://www.booch.com/architecture/blog.jsp">Grady Booch</a>, I am excited to learn that <a href="http://hillside.net/plop/2006/">PLOP 2006</a> and <a href="http://www.oopsla.org/2006/">OOPSLA 2006</a> are in Portland, Oregon,&nbsp;spanning October 21&nbsp;to 26.&nbsp; This is the best opportunity for my attendance&nbsp;since OOPSLA 2002 in Seattle.</small></p><p align="center">{tags: <a href="http://technorati.com/tag/OOPSLA" rel="tag">OOPSLA</a> </strong><a href="http://technorati.com/tag/PLOP" rel="tag">PLOP</a> <a href="http://technorati.com/tag/Peano" rel="tag">Peano</a> <a href="http://technorati.com/tag/interface+contracts" rel="tag">interface contracts</a> <a href="http://technorati.com/tag/abstract+datatypes" rel="tag">abstract datatypes</a> <a href="http://technorati.com/tag/mathematical+objects" rel="tag">mathematical objects</a> <a href="http://technorati.com/tag/orcmid" rel="tag">orcmid</a>}</p><p>There are interesting opportunities for papers (due March 18 for OOPSLA) and pattern work (due May 15 for PLOP).</p><p>In honor of the OOPSLA deadline, I am thinking about crunching the remainder of the Numbering Peano exercise.&nbsp; There&rsquo;s an useful essay in the&nbsp;representation of Peano Numbers by Object-Oriented interfaces.&nbsp; </p><p>I need something to get me out of the doldrums, and this seems like a worthy idea to do that.&nbsp; I also have other promises that I&rsquo;ve made, so I will need to work in parallel.&nbsp; Anything to keep the mind alive!</p><p>I&rsquo;m going to figure this all out on Monday, February 21, after I&nbsp;clean up my systems&nbsp;for this and&nbsp;some other development&nbsp;projects I need to re-energize.</p><p align="center">&nbsp;</p><div style="clear:both; padding-bottom: 0.25em;"></div>
    </p>
	<span class="byline">posted by orcmid
       at <a href="http://miser-theory.info/astraendo/pn/2006/02/moving-peano-ahead-for-oopsla.asp">2/16/2006 07:38:30 PM</a></span>
	       
